After a fierce quest to find the best cheese steak in Philly, I can say that I have found one that qualifies. This quest includes great establishments like Tony Luke's Steaks, Delassandro's Steaks, Geno's Steaks,  Pat's King of Steaks and others.  Ladies and gentleman, after thorough testing and much juice dripping, I have concluded, to this point,  that the best Philly cheese steak is in - Chicago! Yes, Philly's Best in Chicago pumps out winners every time.  Their cheese steaks come in two sizes with grilled onions White American cheese as the default 'configuration'. The meat is so juicy and very tender and the bread is soft and kind of doughy. The sandwich is very oven hot. This is an outstanding cheese steak. The best part about it is that they are consistently great every time.  The owner is from Philadelphia and still sources the ingredients from there.  They offer pizza, fries and sandwiches but for some reason I am stuck on the Philly.  The service is great as well. The cashiers are as nice, and as helpful they can be.  There is an indoor walkway to the neighboring restaurant which is Greek, under ther same ownership. Their offerings look pretty good but for some reason...Philly.  I like this place and I think you will too. This is the best that Philadelphia has to offer. Too bad they're  not in Philadelphia. Ciao
